  "prompt": "Can I get iPhone replaced from Apple Store if it is covered under warranty?",
  "response": "Yes, if your iPhone is covered under Apple's warranty or AppleCare+, you can get it replaced at an Apple Store. Here are some key points:\n\n1. Standard Warranty Coverage:\n- Comes free with every new iPhone\n- Covers manufacturing defects for 1 year from purchase date\n- Provides hardware repair or replacement\n\n2. AppleCare+ Coverage:\n- Extends warranty coverage to 2 years\n- Includes additional benefits like accidental damage protection\n- Lower repair/replacement costs for damaged devices\n\n3. Replacement Process:\n- Book an appointment at Apple Store or Genius Bar\n- Bring your iPhone and proof of purchase/warranty\n- Apple will diagnose the issue\n- If eligible, they'll replace your device on the spot\n\n4. Conditions for Replacement:\n- Must be a manufacturing defect\n- Device must not have unauthorized modifications\n- Battery health must be below a certain threshold\n- Damage from accidents may require additional fees\n\n5. How to Check Warranty Status:\n- Visit Apple's website\n- Enter your device's serial number\n- Check coverage and expiration date\n\nRemember to back up your data before going for a replacement.",
